            <title>[AMQ-2463] Transaction isolation level should be configurable in jdbcpersistence adapter - TRANSACITON_READ_UNCOMMITTED blows on MySQL with binlog</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-2463</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/activemq-dev/200901.mbox/%3C21527285.post@talk.nabble.com%3E&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/activemq-dev/200901.mbox/%3C21527285.post@talk.nabble.com%3E&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;isolation level &amp;gt; READ_COMMITTED needed, like repeatable read for mysql clustered. &lt;a href=&quot;http://bugs.mysql.com/bug.php?id=33210&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://bugs.mysql.com/bug.php?id=33210&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;An int property on the persistence adapter would make this fully configurable&lt;/p&gt;</description>
